Executive Profile
Donald R. Parfet MBAFounder and General Partner, Apjohn Ventures FundAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 14 Board Members in 14 different organizations across 15 different industries.See Board Relationships64--
Background

		Mr. Donald R. Parfet, MBA, also known as Don, is the Founder and General Partner of Apjohn Ventures Fund Limited. Mr. Parfet serves as a Managing Director of Apjohn Group LLC. He served as an Executive Vice President of Administration at Pharmacia & Upjohn Company, LLC. He has over 30 years of experience in all aspects of life sciences business launch, management and exit. He is active in sourcing, governing, accessing and operational and strategic advising pipeline ... and portfolio. He served as Executive Vice President of Administration at Upjohn Co. and served its Senior Vice President of Administration. Mr. Parfet served as the Founding Chief Executive Officer at Afmedica. He served as interim Chief Executive Officer at Sierra Oncology, Inc. from May 2014 to August 2014. He served as a Senior Vice President at Pharmacia. At Pharmacia, his responsibilities included all of the Associated Businesses (Animal Health, Diagnostics, Pharmaceutical Commercial Services and Plasma Products). He oversaw the investments in Amersham Pharmacia Biotech and Biacore International AB. He also had overall site management responsibilities for the company's operations in Kalamazoo, Michigan. He has successfully created a new company through the formation of a joint venture between Amersham and Pharmacia Biotech. He also led a successful $150 million IPO by "spinning out" 60 percent ownership to the public of Biacore International of Sweden. He has spent many years in the Corporate Finance Group of Upjohn Company. He has been the Chairman of Sierra Oncology, Inc. since 2003. He has been the Non-Executive Chairman of Biacore International AB since April 28, 2005 and served as its Deputy Chairman since 2000. He serves as Chairman of Afmedica, Inc., Aursos, Inc., Armune BioScience, Inc., Biosciences Research and Commercialization Center and ProNai. Mr. Parfet served as the Chairman of Bronson Healthcare Group. He serves as Vice Chairman at Bronson Healthcare Group, Inc. He serves as a Director of Southwest Michigan First, AlphaBeta Therapeutics, Inc., Tolera Therapeutics, Inc., Biacore International AB, NephRx Corporation and MPI Research. He serves as an Independent Director at Sierra Oncology, Inc. He has been Independent Director of Masco Corporation since December 4, 2012; Bronson Healthcare Group, Inc., since 1986 and Rockwell Automation Inc. since May 30, 2008 and serves as its Lead Director. He has been an Independent Director of Kelly Services, Inc. since October 4, 2004 and serves as its Lead Director. Mr. Parfet is a Trustee of the W.E. Upjohn Institute for Employment Research. He serves as the Chairman of the Kalamazoo College Board of Trustees. He serves as Board Member of Southwest Michigan Innovation Center and Tetra Discovery Partners LLC. He holds an MBA degree in Finance from the University of Michigan in 1977 and a B.A. degree in Economics from the University of Arizona in 1975.Read Full Background




