Insider Activity


Individual




Donald R. Parfet



Mr. Don R. Parfet is Co-Founder & General Partner at Apjohn Ventures LLC, a Managing Director at Apjohn Group LLC, Chairman at Biosciences Research & Commercialization Center, Chairman at ProNAi Therapeutics, Inc., a Director at Southwest Michigan First, Chairman at Aursos, Inc., and President at MedElute, Inc. He is on the Board of Directors at Rockwell Automation, Inc., Kelly Services, Inc., Bronson Health Care Group, Inc., NephRx Corp., Tolera Therapeutics, Inc., and Axenic Dental, Inc.
Mr. Parfet was previously employed as Senior Vice President by Pharmacia Corp., Chairman by Biacore International AB, and Chief Executive Officer by Pharmacia & Upjohn, Inc.
Mr. Parfet received his BA degree in Economics from the University of Arizona in 1975 and his M.B.A. degree in Finance from the University of Michigan in 1977.



